  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-8 main-col">
      <section class="intro">
        <p class="lead">This place is excellent. The parking situation could be better, with warnings regarding parking anywhere other than four spots near the deck, but figure it out, and go inside. It’s worth it.</p>
        <p>Other than the giant maracas painted on the side of the building we saw no actual maracas(es?) maraca (?) inside, which was a relief. There are no frills: just laminate tables, an unseen bar behind a wall, two main dining rooms and a large outside patio/deck which is enclosed with Visqueen (often misspelled visquine) for the winter months. Food and drink specials appear daily. Notably adding to the vibe were a caballero, four loud drunks and a bunch of families. The menu is hilariously oversized - even for your standard Mexican restaurant. Counting specials, one could eat at Las Maracas three times a week for an entire year and never order the same thing.</p>
      </section>

